{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3154977,"name":"Ben Gold","username":"bgold","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/b/cab0a1/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-03-01T02:14:58.585Z","cooked":"<p>We’ve been trying to use the WPILib implementation of pose detection, using basically the code that was described here, along with the AprilTagPoseEstimator:</p>
<aside class="quote" data-post="1" data-topic="421411">
  <div class="title">
    <div class="quote-controls"></div>
    <img loading="lazy" alt="" width="24" height="24" src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/mikets/48/4625_2.png" class="avatar">
    <a href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/wpilib-apriltagdetector-sample-code/421411">WPILIB AprilTagDetector sample code</a> <a class="badge-category__wrapper " href="/c/technical/programming/30"><span data-category-id="30" style="--category-badge-color: #F7941D; --category-badge-text-color: #FFF; --parent-category-badge-color: #3AB54A;" data-parent-category-id="9" data-drop-close="true" class="badge-category --has-parent" title="Discussion of any ideas, algorithms, etc."><span class="badge-category__name">Programming</span></span></a>
  </div>
  <blockquote>
    I did a quick scan on the released WPILib and found several AprilTag related classes, but the JavaDoc is practically useless because their descriptions are basically repeating the name of the methods without any explanation what they actually do and their parameters. I am looking for sample code on how to use these classes and methods but found none. Can somebody point us to sample code calling these classes to create an AprilTag pipeline?
  </blockquote>
</aside>

<p>But the numbers aren’t making sense, for instance the “z” of the resulting pose estimate changes as the camera moves up and down the Y axis (vertical). The “x” of the pose estimate will change as the camera rotates around the Y axis.</p>
<p>Is this expected? Are there expected transformations that should be applied after the detection like I’ve seen with the PhotonVision code?</p>
<p>Thanks for any help!</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":3,"updated_at":"2023-03-01T02:14:58.585Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":44,"reads":107,"readers_count":106,"score":241.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":428509,"topic_slug":"what-is-apriltag-poseestimator-returning","display_username":"Ben Gold","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/wpilib-apriltagdetector-sample-code/421411","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"WPILIB AprilTagDetector sample code","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":57481,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/what-is-apriltag-poseestimator-returning/428509/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3155144,"name":"","username":"dardeshna","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/dardeshna/{size}/8532_2.png","created_at":"2023-03-01T05:56:51.570Z","cooked":"<p>I was confused by the same thing the other day when using apriltags for a class project.  So then I looked at how Photon and WPILib handle it.  The conclusion I came to was that the apriltag convention is East-Down-North (also opencv’s convention) while I was trying to use North-West-Up (NWU) which is also WPILib’s convention.  There is also one more 180° flip that has to be done because the apriltag library assumes an inward-facing normal.</p>
<p>Here’s what I ended up with in WPILib sim before I went back to my own project.  Photon also has their <a href="https://github.com/PhotonVision/photonvision/blob/master/photon-core/src/main/java/org/photonvision/common/util/math/MathUtils.java" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">MathUtils</a> code which implements similar functions.  Good luck!</p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">Transform3d convertAprilTagTransformtoWpilibTransform(Transform3d aprilTagTransform) {

    Rotation3d NWUtoEDN = CoordinateSystem.convert(new Rotation3d(), CoordinateSystem.EDN(), CoordinateSystem.NWU());

    return new Transform3d(
        CoordinateSystem.convert(aprilTagTransform.getTranslation(), CoordinateSystem.EDN(), CoordinateSystem.NWU()),
        new Rotation3d(0, 0, Math.PI).plus(NWUtoEDN.unaryMinus()).plus(aprilTagTransform.getRotation()).plus(NWUtoEDN)
    );
}
</code></pre>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":3,"updated_at":"2023-03-01T05:56:51.570Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":20,"reads":81,"readers_count":80,"score":146.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":428509,"topic_slug":"what-is-apriltag-poseestimator-returning","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/PhotonVision/photonvision/blob/master/photon-core/src/main/java/org/photonvision/common/util/math/MathUtils.java","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"photonvision/MathUtils.java at master · PhotonVision/photonvision · GitHub","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":26092,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/what-is-apriltag-poseestimator-returning/428509/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3320361,"name":"system","username":"system","avatar_template":"/uploads/default/original/4X/9/3/2/93234578e69f55873c63fc00fe2d0d85f23bce55.png","created_at":"2024-02-29T05:57:43.578Z","cooked":"<p>This topic was automatically closed 365 days after the last reply. New replies are no longer allowed.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":3,"posts_count":3,"updated_at":"2024-02-29T05:57:43.578Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_